          <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Hd1e108">Rubrica 8</head>
          <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De miseria et miseris</head>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e114">
             <lb ed="#O"/>De miseria et miseris. Rubrica. 8.
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e119">
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e116">IOb hystoria. capitulo 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e123">Deus ponit 
             <lb ed="#O"/>humiles in sublime et meren$tes 
             erigit sospitate.</quote> 
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e131"> 
             % <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e128">36. capitulo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e133">quidam 
             <lb ed="#O"/>amicorum iob. nomine eliu in consolatione 
             <lb ed="#O"/>iob dixit ei. % Caue ne declines 
             <lb ed="#O"/>iniquitatem. Hanc enim cepisti sequi 
             <lb ed="#O"/>post miseriam.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e141">
    <!--paragraph omitted-->
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e145">Salomon in prouerbiis. capitulo 19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e147">Homo 
             indigens misericors est.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e148">
    <!--paragraph omitted-->
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e157">Salustius in iugurtino</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e152">Expertus sum 
             parum fidei miseris esse.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e158">
    <!--paragraph omitted-->
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e169">Tullius paradoxorum distinctione. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e162">Ut improbo et 
             stulto et inerti nemini bene esse potest Sic bonus uir
             et fortis et sapiens miser esse non potest.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e170">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e183">OUidius <!--line bumps up--> de ponto. libro 2. epistola 7.</ref> <!--line bumps back down--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e174">res timida est omnis 
             <lb ed="#O"/>miser.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e180"> 
             % <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e193">libro. 4. et finali. epistola 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e182">Nil adeo 
             <lb ed="#O"/>fortuna grauis miserabile fecit
             <lb ed="#O"/>Ut muniant nulla gaudia perte
             <lb ed="#O"/>malum.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e190">
             % <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e207">epistola. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e194">Crede mihi miseros 
             <lb ed="#O"/>prudentia summa reliquit. Et sen$sus 
             cum re consiliumque fugit.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e202">
             % <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e222">
             <lb ed="#O"/>Idem de nuce.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e206">Quam miserum est odium 
             <lb ed="#O"/>dampnis accedere nostris.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e213">
             <!--line bumps down-->
             <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e234">QUintilianus decla<!--line bumps up-->mationum. 1. declamatione.</ref> <!--line bumps back down--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e217">Semper ibi 
             <lb ed="#O"/>custodiunt minseri ne esse miser$abiles 
             desinant.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e225"> 
             % <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e246">13. declamatione.</ref> 
             <lb ed="#O"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e227">leuior est calamitas cui blanditur 
             <lb ed="#O"/>aliquid de uoluptate letitia.</quote>
          </p>
  <!--LEFT OFF HERE-->
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e233">
             <ref><!--add xml tag-->Seneca tragediarum in thieste. capitulo 11.</ref>
             <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e237">Proprium hoc miseros sequitur uicium.
             Nunquam rebus crede letis.
             Redere felix fortuna licet.
             Tamen afflictos gaudere piget.
             Flendi miseris dira cupido est.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e251">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e276">In troa. capitulo 12. et penultimo.</ref>
             <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e255">Nemo se credit miserum sit licet. 
             Tolle felices.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e267">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e294">Idem epistolarum ad lucillum. libro 9. epistola i.</ref>
             <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e271">Nemo nisi uicio miser est.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e277">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e307">Idem declamationum. libro 8. capitulo 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e281">Fortuna quos 
             miseros facit etiam superstitiosos facit.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e288">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e319">Lucanus. libro 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e292">Seruat multos fortuma 
             nocentes. Et tantum miseris irasci numina possunt.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e298">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e331">Statius <sic>thebaydos</sic> libro 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e302">Hic miseris 
             furor est: astare periculo. Nec librare metus et tu
             ta odisse. Quid causus iuuat ostentare pudentes</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e310">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e345">libro 12</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e314">Amant miseri lamenta malisque fruuntur.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e318">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e355">Fulgentius. libro 1. fabula 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e322">Sola est medicina
             minseriarum obliuio.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e328">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e367">Boetius de consolatione. libro i. capitulo 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e332">Hic etiam 
             uestris cumulis malis accedit quod existimatio
             plurimorum non rerum merita sed fortune spectat 
             euentum. eaque tantum iudicat esse prouisa qui felicitas 
             commendauerit. Quo fit ut existimatio bona prima 
             omnium deserat infelices. Hoc tantum dixerim ultimam
             esse aduerse fortune sarcinam quod dum 
             miseris aliquod crimen affigitur que proferuntur
             meruisse redduntur.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e353">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e395">Cassiodorus epistolarum libro 5. epistola 29.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e357">Necesse est
             ut amplius permoueat uisa quam audita calamitas.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e366"> 
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e407">36. epistola.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e368">Non est ignauie culpa quam excusat miseranda calamitas.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e374"> 
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e417">libro 10. epistola 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e376">Deus 
             consueuit casus asperos in prospera commutare.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e382">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e429">Auctor libelli qui dicitur pamphylus. capitulo 18.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e386">Parua
             nocent miseris miseros mala multa sequuntur.
             Spesque laborque suus remanent in dubio.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e394">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e443">Gualterius de castellione. libro 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e398">Sors 
             miseri querula est.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e404">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e455">Iacobus beneuentanus. capitulo 52.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e408">Ludibrium
             populo fit miser omnis homo.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e414">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e468">Prouerbia metricum extraordinem librorum uagantia.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e418">
             Solatium est miseris socios habere penarum.</quote>
          </p>
          <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e425">
             <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Rd1e480">Prouerbia uulgaria.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e429">Ai cham magri uale mosche.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
